Undirected arcs in the consensus network were classified as representing either positive (inclusive) or negative (exclusive) associations between PNGS, as determined by calculating the posterior odds-ratios from the corresponding 2 × 2 contingency tables of posterior parameters. For example, the contingency table for the PNGSs N411 and N413 contained the following:
